ActFederal Real Property and Federal Immovables Act
Other Than Statutory Authority
SubjectCreation of Carp South Indian Reserve No. 7 (British Columbia)
PrecisOrder (1) accepting on behalf of Her Majesty in right of Canada, the transfer of administration and control from Her Majesty in right of British Columbia, of the entire interest in certain lands; and (2) setting apart 2,328.53 hectares (5,753.92 acres) of land, excluding mines and minerals, for the use and benefit of the MCLEOD LAKE INDIAN BAND, as CARP SOUTH INDIAN RESERVE No. 7, in British Columbia.
